 Austin Karonga 
SPORTS WRITER 
karongaa@dailynews.co.zw THE National Federation of Zimbabwe Bodybuilding and Fitness (NFZBF) is planning to host a powerlifting competition in order to put an end to a number of arguments currently engulfing the industry. Veteran bodybuilders Collin Mushunje and Prosper Saungweme have in recent weeks challenged the upcoming generation led by Simbarashe Godwin Mhaka to a powerlifting contest. Seasoned bodybuilders have argued that there is a positive correlation between hypertrophy and improvements in power and strength. 